<paragraph id="8BD0CA0BFFD7FFA00E5C48F665D870EB" blockId="2.[813,1420,809,1224]" pageId="2" pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicName id="4C6FB188FFD7FFA00E5C48F6650B77BF" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1842" box="[850,1081,900,924]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barbodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="317" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lateristriga">
<emphasis id="B91B1619FFD7FFA00E5C48F6650B77BF" box="[850,1081,900,924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="317">Barbodes lateristriga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be identified by the lateral markings usually forming a solid stripe and no streak extending from the operculum (vs prominent row of dark spots along the lateral line, plus a short and horizon- tally orientated streak extending from the upper part of the operculum in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FB188FFD7FFA00EE14F5E65AA7060" baseAuthorityName="Herre" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1007,1176,1067,1091]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barbodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="317" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuchingensis">
<emphasis id="B91B1619FFD7FFA00EE14F5E65AA7060" box="[1007,1176,1067,1091]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="317">B. kuchingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This species usually inhabit clear mountain streams strewn with rocks and boulders, and frequently found below waterfalls (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEB7FAFFD7FFA008394F1C62547084" author="Roberts TR" pageId="2" pageNumber="317" pagination="1 - 210" refId="ref9139" refString="Roberts TR (1989) The freshwater fishes of Western Borneo (Kaliman- tan Barat, Indonesia). Memoirs of the Southern California Acad- emy of Sciences 14: 1 - 210." type="journal article" year="1989">Roberts 1989</bibRefCitation>
). This species feeds on worms, crustaceans, insects and plant matter (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEB7FAFFD7FFA00EE64FC265EF70EB" author="Mills D &amp; Vevers G" box="[1000,1245,1200,1224]" pageId="2" pageNumber="317" refId="ref8492" refString="Mills D, Vevers G (1989) The Tetra encyclopedia of freshwater tropical aquarium fishes. Tetra Press, Morris Plains, NJ, 208 pp." type="book" year="1989">Mills and Vevers 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
